= Projects used by PBS

== AllInOneRuby
* Erik Veenstra <allinoneruby@erikveen.dds.nl>
* http://rubyforge.org/projects/allinoneruby/
* Used to release Ruby for platforms missing Ruby

== Exerb
* Yuya Kato <yuyakato@gmail.com>
* http://exerb.sourceforge.jp/index.en.html
* Used to create the executable entry point of PBS

== Nokogiri
* Aaron Patterson (http://tenderlovemaking.com/)
* Mike Dalessio (http://mike.daless.io/)
* http://nokogiri.rubyforge.org/nokogiri/
* Used to parse HTML in HTML import plugin

== NSIS
* kichik@users.sourceforge.net
* http://nsis.sourceforge.net
* Used to create the installer for Windows

== Ocra
* Lars Christensen
* http://rubyforge.org/projects/ocra/
* Used its edicon utility to change executable icon

== Ruby
* Yukihiro « matz » Matsumoto (http://www.rubyist.net/~matz/)
* http://www.ruby-lang.org/
* Used to develop PBS. Thanks a lot Matz for this truly wonderful language !

== RubyGems
* Paul Duncan <pabs@pablotron.org>
* http://rubygems.org/
* Used to automatically download Gem dependencies

== RubyZip
* Thomas Sondergaard <thomas@sondergaard.cc>
* Technorama Ltd. <oss-ruby-zip@technorama.net>
* Tatsuki Sugiura <sugi@nemui.org>
* http://rubyzip.sourceforge.net/
* Used to unzip dependencies downloaded from the web

== SQLite3-Ruby
* Jamis Buck
* http://rubyforge.org/projects/sqlite-ruby/
* Used to read SQLite3 databases in Firefox and Chrome import plugins

== WxRuby
* Sean Long (http://rubyforge.org/users/seanlong/)
* Alex Fenton (http://rubyforge.org/users/brokentoy/)
* http://wxruby.rubyforge.org
* Used as the GUI framework

= People that helped a lot in developing PBS

* ACM, for her testing during difficult Alpha releases
* Jeremy Hinegardner <jeremy@hinegardner.org>, for his wonderful project Crate that should be the next standard in shipping cross-platform ruby applications
* Alex Fenton (http://rubyforge.org/users/brokentoy/) for his unvaluable help in better understanding WxRuby and WxWidgets
